### Potential Pitfalls and Mitigations

**1. `instanceof` checks across module boundaries.** Since this project uses ES modules (not CommonJS) and the error classes will be defined in a single `errors.ts` file imported by both service and route modules, `instanceof` will work correctly. There is no bundling or transpilation that would break prototype chains.

